data.description: Welcome home to this beautiful, like new,  traditional style Regency home, where no stone was left unturned during construction. Located in the lovely neighborhood of Stonecrest and highly sought after Pleasant Hill Elementary and DeSoto Central School district, you're sure to be pleased as you walk through the oversized french doors. You'll be greeted by an open floor plan, wood flooring, spacious dining room, living room, and eat-in kitchen complete with organizer pull out drawers, a lazy susan, bullnose granite countertops, backsplash, and a pantry. In the living room you'll find built in bookshelves and cabinets on both sides of the gas fireplace, smooth vaulted ceilings, and the perfect view of the upstairs loft area with stunning wrought iron railing. Storage is not a problem in this home as the long hallway leading to the primary bedroom offers a shelved closet and mudroom. The primary bedroom with a well sized walk-in is just the beginning to a day of relaxation as you enter into the large primary en suite with double vanities, a walk through shower, and a second well sized closet. As you walk up the wood stairs, you'll find the loft overlooking the living room, three large bedrooms, one of which can be used as a bonus room which leads to a handsomely sized expandable room. Need a breath of fresh air and more relaxation, no problem, relax by the bricked gas fireplace in the screened-in back patio. No need to look any further, your home is here at 5900 Stonecrest Dr. Come on in!
